<div>
  <h1 class="front_page_col_header">What is iGUESS?</h1>

  <div class="front_page_col_body">
    iGUESS is a web based spatial decision support platform for urban energy planning.
    European cities are in need of comprehensive geospatial tools to develop and implement
    their carbon-reductive planning and policies and to monitor the progress they make.
    With iGUESS, cities will be able to compute and visualise energy consumption and
    their related CO2 emissions, identify opportunities for balancing energy sources and
    sinks via scenarios and monitor the effects of energy saving measures in their city.
    iGUESS will help your city to:

    <ul>
      <li>compute and visualise urban energy maps, with information on costs, consump-
        tion and emissions;
      <li>support urban planning by identifying of renewable energy potentials, e.g. solar,
        wind, geothermal, heat;
      <li>evelop and test different scenarios and optimise a cityâ€™s energy system;
      <li>monitor emission mitigation actions.
    </ul>
  </div>

